title: 820-00163 powers up no chime or display, question on power rail variations
message: Hi, ive got an 820-00163 powers up no chime or display ive checked every power rail and all are correct except some variations on pp1v35_gpu_reg which should be 1.35v and i have 1.48v, ppvddc1_so_isense should be 1.12v and i have 0.9v and ppvcore_gpu which should be 1v and i have 0.84v could this be enough of a difference to cause a problem ?? , i did have a look at pp1v35_gpu_reg and found that the voltage at L8710 should be 1.05v according to the schematic but i have 1.48v , could this mean that q8710 or u8700 could be at fault or is the schematic off on voltage and im just gonna get headache :-) P.S this board has no signs of any damage anywhere
